Kong strikes some King-like poses and says 'Hey you little people, get off my lawn'.  The End?  Overall I am getting a better feel for Kong: Skull Island and it might be pretty good.  Would like more Tom Hiddleston and Brie Larson, less Samuel L. Jackson and John Goodman (just because I'm pretty sure their characters are what you see in the trailers) and more of the Giant Yak.  I mean, c'mon.  A Giant Yak?  You've got steak houses already flying to the location shoot to see if they can find evidence that Giant Burger/Steak factories do walk the earth.  I really need another trailer to lock in what Tom and Brie's character arcs are going to look like on screen aside from the descriptions from earlier reports on the movie.   Gotta pretty good feeling so far.  More to come, I hope.

text: So yes, agreed, the trailer does have some tone issues. But it IS just a trailer. Looks like the movie has a lot payoff in terms of actually seeing the monsters in action. That could go well or poorly depending on what type of viewer you are. Personally, I've always been frustrated by the tease method but it DOES amplify those moments you do get to extreme awesomeness. I'll be seeing this one but I think it's a safer bet to check your expectations at the door. Looks more "entertaining" than it does "substantial" so far (it's giant monsters fighting and stuff, so that makes sense haha).  Just my 2c. Cheers y'all.
